		<h2>Methodology</h2>
		<p><strong>Emotional Securities</strong> is an experimental analysis of general sentiment towards a given company against stock price of said company.</p>
		<p>Working off a few of the core metrics of behavioral finance, we pulled "herd" sentiment data from the Twitter Streaming API, and "expert" sentiment from articles on Yahoo Finance. AlchemyAPI kindly granted us academic access to their amazing service, which we used to analyze sentiment in tweets, and entity targeted sentiment in articles.</p>
		<p>We have implimented an attempt at a Na√Øve Bayes algorithm to try to sort through relevant tweets; our algorithm, fondly nicknamed Hal9000, is given a sampling of "expert" tweets, and non-related tweets. It learns what words and phrases are commonly used in the relevant tweets, and sorts our incoming stream based on that data.</p> 
